description:
Hudson Institute is seeking a full-time intern to support the Institute's work on issues surrounding the role of history in formulating American grand strategy and improving national security. In addition to being exposed to critical issues in these fields, interns will spend significant time discussing these issues with their scholar. Onsite interns also attend weekly events featuring experts from Hudson Institute and across Washington, DC. Applicants should have a strong interest in American and European history, as well as knowledge of diplomatic and military history. A strong background in research, writing, and editing is preferred.

Responsibilities
Gathering and analyzing data for inclusion in reports and articles;
Keeping the scholar and team up to date on current events;
Assisting the scholar with research projects and presentations;
Assisting with articles, op-eds, reports, and briefing papers;
Assisting with administrative tasks and event support.

Not everyone who works for a global company shares the same background, experiences and perspectives. We leverage the differences of our employees to bring new ideas to the table. Every employee throughout the company is encouraged to share input on projects and initiatives. Our decision making process is truly a collaborative effort as we realize there are leaders at every level of the organization. We put our values at the core of how we operate as an organization — not just when it’s convenient, but in a lasting and meaningful way. We want the time and energy you spend here to have a positive impact on your life inside and outside of the office.

Entegris is a values-driven culture and our employees rally around our core PACE values:

People 
Accountability

Creativity 
Excellence

Entegris is currently seeking a talented and innovative Scientist to join its Analytical & Metrology team in Billerica, MA.

This role will focus on the trace metal analysis to support membrane R&D and new liquid filtration and purification products development in the Micro-contamination Control (MC) Division of Entegris. The Scientist serves as a subject matter expert related to the characterization of trace metal contaminants for semiconductor applications. In line with our values, which is fostering an environment of teamwork, you will have an opportunity to collaborate with a talented global team of engineers and scientists to solve challenge tasks.

The ideal candidate will be results oriented and an excellent team player, with solid knowledge of analytical chemistry & inorganic chemistry, and familiar with semiconductor device materials, structures, and metrology.

Perform trace metal analysis using ICP-MS;
Develop ICP-MS methods drive for continuous improvement of existing testing methods;
Use product and testing expertise to collaborate with internal and external customers to determine root causes in product development and quality problems;
Collaborate with application team to solve customer quality complaints and provide solutions to their technical issues;
Promote Entegris’ image by participating in industrial conferences and seminars;
Continuous training on the various analytical techniques and methods;
Document work in internal reporting systems, and external publications.

Due to Federal monitor agreement, Healthy Homes is seeking a Communications Coordinator as liaison to keep lines of communication open with other departments; to ensure meaningful collaboration; to facilitate communications with stakeholders, reports on activity, maintains visibility of strategic planning process and effective implementation, as well as to coordinate resources across multiple departments in strategic planning efforts. In addition, to provide support and direction as appropriate.

Assignment Duties
Develop, track, coordinate & facilitate communications with stakeholders;
Designs strategies to mitigate or avoid risks.
Coordinates resources across multiple departments
reports on activity; performs outreach to Pillar teams, NYCHA's depart & other agencies;
track indicators related to outcomes of the strategic planning process;
monitors project, program, and assesses impact to strategic initiatives; escalates issues as appropriate.

Vecoplan, LLC is seeking a Marketing Assistant to serve as an integral player in all marketing department activities. This person will be responsible for his or her own projects combined with general support on both short- and long-term initiatives driven by the department director. This is a salaried position reporting to the Marketing Director.

Responsibilities:
Create, contribute, and/or assist in various marketing campaigns to support each sales segment;
Manage the company’s digital and social media while adhering to department’s strategy and brand;
Track campaign performance and generate performance reports;
Assist in event (physical and virtual) preparation including presentations, pulling and packaging items for shipment;
Maintain marketing lists;
Contribute to department’s creativity through new ideas and information based on his or her own research;
Understand the company’s product, customer base and target audiences;
Track and record departmental costs;
Heed sense of urgency as projects dictate;
Work closely with the director to complete projects in a timely fashion;
Provide administrative and general support to department director.
